<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3A6A85F820932D1415BD64" pageId="193" pageNumber="955" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3A6A85F820932D1415BD64" blockId="193.[2010,2605,1273,1701]" pageId="193" pageNumber="955">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3A6A85F78C932D16C4BEA3" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[2160,2244,1396,1425]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="955" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3A6A85F72B932D1761BEA3" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[2263,2401,1396,1425]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="955" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mystacinus">mystacinus</taxonomicName>
species group (4 species), which may besister to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3A6A85F64393C5142DBE8B" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[2495,2605,1436,1465]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="955" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">muricola</taxonomicName>
species group. This species appears to be sister to M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3A6A85F77B93BF16F6BD35" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[2183,2294,1510,1543]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="955" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altarium">altarium</taxonomicName>
. Previously treated as a race of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3A6A85F79F90571704BD1D" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[2147,2308,1550,1583]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="193" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
, but split on genetic and morphological grounds. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
